A Comparison of Sound Onset Detection Algorithms with Emphasis on Psychoacoustically Motivated Detection Functions

@article{Collins2005ACO,
  title={A Comparison of Sound Onset Detection Algorithms with Emphasis on Psychoacoustically Motivated Detection Functions},
  author={N. M. Collins},
  journal={Journal of The Audio Engineering Society},
  year={2005}
}
  • N. Collins
  • Published 1 May 2005
  • Computer Science
  • Journal of The Audio Engineering Society
Whilst many onset detection algorithms for musical events in audio signals have been proposed, comparative studies of their efficacy for segmentation tasks are much rarer. This paper follows the lead of Bello et al. 04, using the same hand marked test database as a benchmark for comparison. That previous paper did not include in the comparison a psychoacoustically motivated algorithm originally proposed by Klapuri in 1999, an oversight which is corrected herein with respect to a number of…
